## Django Standards

- Use class-based views (CBV) or Django REST Framework `APIView`/`ViewSet` for new endpoints
- Keep business logic in service modules (`services.py`), not in models or views
- Use Django's ORM for all database operations; avoid raw SQL unless profiling justifies it
- Use `select_related` and `prefetch_related` to avoid N+1 queries
- Define serializers with explicit field lists; never use `fields = "__all__"` in production
- Write model migrations for every schema change; never edit existing migrations
- Use Django's `test.TestCase` with a test database; isolate tests with `@override_settings`
